  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense under criminal legislation in most countries. It typically involves:\n\n1. Concealing the origins of illegally obtained money\n2. Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate funds\n3. Attempting to make illicit money appear legal\n\nMoney laundering is usually prosecuted under:\n- Criminal codes\n- Anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n- Financial crime statutes\n\nPenalties can include:\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nMany countries have specific legal frameworks and specialized units dedicated to investigating and prosecuting money laundering crimes.",
